% You are an expert Python engineer. Your goal is to write `pdd/server/budget.py`.

% Role & Scope
  This module implements the `/pdd` comment-command control surface for
  GitHub App-triggered PDD runs. It parses comments posted on issues/PRs
  during an active run, maintains the per-job `BudgetState` (per-node
  budget, max total cap, accumulated spend, status), formats the startup
  comment that the App posts when a run begins, formats the `/pdd settings`
  read-only reply, and provides a `should_halt` predicate that the
  executor consults after each chunk of work to stop runs whose accumulated
  spend has reached the active cap. This module owns budget parsing,
  state, formatting, and the halt predicate — it does NOT own GitHub API
  calls, executor cost capture, or job lifecycle.

